cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category as it deals with improving speech recognition by learning acoustic features. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves improving phonetic recognition accuracies. The use of deep learning methods suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the analysis of design choices could suggest it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as this is a common theme in image processing and computer vision research.
